Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "brzina" in different forms and positions:

1. *Brzina* je bitna u trkama. (Speed is important in races.)
2. Vozim brzo, ali ne prekoračujem *brzinu*. (I'm driving fast, but I'm not exceeding the speed limit.)
3. Železnička stanica ima ograničenje *brzine* zbog bezbednosti putnika. (The railway station has a speed limit for the safety of passengers.)
4. Pogledaj kojom *brzinom* leti taj avion! (Look at how fast that plane is flying!)
5. Vožnja pri velikim *brzinama* može biti opasna. (Driving at high speeds can be dangerous.)
6. *Brzine* automobila se mogu podešavati ručno ili automatski. (The speeds of cars can be adjusted manually or automatically.)
7. Potrebno je da se pridržavate propisane *brzine* u gradu. (You need to adhere to the prescribed speed limit in the city.)
8. Ona je brza trkačica, ali još uvek treba da radi na *brzini*. (She's a fast runner, but she still needs to work on her speed.)

I hope this helps!